  "body": "Maybe this is the intended behavior but it leads to user errors when they type private repositories \"wrong\" (like with `helm repo add foo  https://host.com` instead of `helm repo add foo  https://host.com/` or within the `requirements.yaml`).\r\n\r\nExample:\r\n-----------\r\n~/.helm/repository/repositories.yaml \r\n```yaml\r\napiVersion: v1\r\ngenerated: 2016-11-21T14:16:06.747386772+01:00\r\nrepositories:\r\n- cache: stable-index.yaml\r\n  name: stable\r\n  url: https://kubernetes-charts.storage.googleapis.com/\r\n```\r\n\r\nrequirements.yaml\r\n```yaml\r\ndependencies:\r\n  - name: redis\r\n    version: 0.1.1\r\n    repository: https://kubernetes-charts.storage.googleapis.com\r\n```\r\n\r\n```bash\r\n$ helm dependency build  .\r\nError: no repository definition for https://kubernetes-charts.storage.googleapis.com. Try 'helm repo add'\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis could be fixed by always removing the trailing slash when comparing URLs but I'm unsure if this is always the correct solution\r\n\r\n```patch\r\ndiff --git a/cmd/helm/downloader/manager.go b/cmd/helm/downloader/manager.go\r\nindex db3d3c4..c35264d 100644\r\n--- a/cmd/helm/downloader/manager.go\r\n+++ b/cmd/helm/downloader/manager.go\r\n@@ -320,6 +320,14 @@ func urlsAreEqual(a, b string) bool {\r\n        if err != nil {\r\n                return false\r\n        }\r\n+       // Make sure URLs with or without trailing slash are threated equal\r\n+       if au.Path == \"/\" {\r\n+               au.Path = \"\"\r\n+       }\r\n+       if bu.Path == \"/\" {\r\n+               bu.Path = \"\"\r\n+       }\r\n+\r\n        return au.String() == bu.String()\r\n }\r\n```\r\n",
